Opening and ending a film with a dog should be how all films should be made.
Kinda awkward and cringeðŸ˜¬so surface level it's s kiddie's pool, but you'd say that's the point. A film to watch with friends to have a good laugh, then we'll go back to our phones.
That scene with the trombone... I fell in love again. We need Koreeda's humanity.

Jaw-dropping movie with no respect for the characters and has a story with questionable politics. It seems like the movie blames the wrong people for the violence that erupted and it also want to make a cinematic experience out of their self-destruction? As if they deserved it? That's just exploitation.Also the soundtrack was overused.
As Little Bush said "the movies gives us exquisite sex and wholesome violence."Ti West and Bush would be horrible table companions.

Good breakup movie. I felt so sad and lonely at times. It was dragging a bit here and there. +1 for border collie dog. Men are complicated and it gets worse when they get a drink, because then, they'll become intellectual men.Also, I was so sure the movie was set in the 21st century, I was expecting some people to whip out their smartphone.

I feel happy if a crazy movie like that can still be made. It's enough for me if it exists, I won't ask for more from it. Everyone was good in the film (some performances overshadow others), lovely music, good characters (but wished I had more time with them), no time to catch a breath (headache by the end).
